# .npmignore — what to EXCLUDE from the npm tarball.
#
# The npm package is a deprecated friendly-error shim: bin/backpropagate.js
# prints install guidance for pipx / uv tool / pip and exits 2. No runtime
# dependencies. Only the shim + READMEs + LICENSE need to ship; everything
# else stays on GitHub. History: v1.0–v1.2 used @mcptoolshop/npm-launcher
# to bootstrap PyInstaller binaries; the binary pipeline failed three
# consecutive times in v1.2.0, so v1.3 retires that path and the launcher
# dependency was dropped.
#
# KNOWN LIMITATION: npm has a hardcoded "always include" rule for files
# matching ^(README|LICENSE|CHANGELOG|NOTICE|HISTORY)(\..*)?$ — listing them
# here does NOT exclude them. Net effect: all 8 README files (English +
# 7 translations) are bundled into the tarball (~60KB total).  Acceptable
# for v1.1.0; iterate the shape in v1.1.x if the bloat becomes a concern.

# Python source — not needed in the Node-side wrapper
backpropagate/
tests/
docs/
site/
scripts/
examples/
assets/

# Long-form ops docs (available via GitHub + PyPI)
ROADMAP.md
SHIP_GATE.md
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
PRODUCTION_READINESS_AUDIT.md
SECURITY_AUDIT_REPORT.md
SECURITY.md
CLAUDE.md
llms.txt
logo.png

# Python build / config artifacts
pyproject.toml
uv.lock
verify.sh
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
.pre-commit-config.yaml
.secrets.baseline
_config.yml

# Workflow + dev hygiene
.github/
.gitignore
.claude/

# Reflex working dir + Python caches (also covered by .gitignore;
# belt + suspenders for npm tarball)
.web/
.states
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
